# Docker Commands : 

1. Docker Version Check
docker --version

2. Docker Installation
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install docker.io

3. Docker Service Status
systemctl status docker

4. User Group Management
sudo usermod -aG docker ubuntu (to add user ubuntu to the Docker group)
newgrp docker (to refresh group permissions)

5. Managing Containers
docker ps (list running containers)
docker images (list available images)
docker kill <container_id> (stop a container)
docker rm <container_id> (remove a container)

6. Building and Running Docker Images
docker build -t java-app . (build a Docker image from the Dockerfile)
docker run java-app:latest (run the built Java application container)

7. Directory Navigation
Navigated through directories related to a Java project:
cd github/
cd simple-java-docker/src
pwd (print working directory)

8. Dockerfile Management
vim Dockerfile (open Dockerfile in vim)
cat Dockerfile (display contents of the Dockerfile)
rm Dockerfile (remove the Dockerfile)
